records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years.  That is four (4) years initial confinement followed by four (4) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  He is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately upon completion of the jail sentences imposed on 16 CF 529, 16 CF 108, 16 CF 442 and 16 CF 314;
2) Provide DNA sample;
3) Pay court costs including $100.00 buy money to Metro Drug;
4) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling combination;
8) Maintain absolute sobriety;
9) Defendant is to have no association with any known drug users or dealers;
10) Defendant is to use only one doctor to prescribe medications and one pharmacist to dispense medications.
Minutes.

Attorney Wingrove states that the defendant no longer wishes him to withdraw from this matter.  The Court vacates the order to withdraw and indicates that Attorney Wingrove will continue as attorney in this case.
The defendant has not made himself available for the competency examination.  The defendant has been living with a lady who threw out his mail and turned off his phone, thats why he didnt show up for his appointment.  Another appointment has been set up for next week.    The parties are asking that bail be modified to include that the defendant must reside with his mother.
The Court modifies the conditions of bail to include:
-that he must reside with his mother, Patty Reznichek, at 908 S. 37th Street, Manitowoc, WI; 
-defendant must cooperate with the Wisconsin Forensic Unit and show up for all scheduled appointments; 
-defendant is to have a working, active phone throughout this case; 
-maintain absolute sobriety and have no possession of any controlled substance unless prescribed by a physician.
Minutes.
